    <h1>Hiring Process Documentation</h1>
    <p>This document outlines the steps involved in the hiring process for our organization.</p>

    <h2>1. Job Posting</h2>
    <p>The hiring process begins with creating and publishing a job posting. This includes:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Defining the job title, responsibilities, and qualifications.</li>
        <li>Posting the job on relevant platforms (e.g., company website, job boards).</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. Application Screening</h2>
    <p>Once applications are received, the screening process involves:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Reviewing resumes and cover letters.</li>
        <li>Shortlisting candidates who meet the job requirements.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. Initial Interview</h2>
    <p>Shortlisted candidates are invited for an initial interview. This step includes:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Conducting phone or video interviews to assess basic qualifications.</li>
        <li>Discussing the candidate's experience and expectations.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Technical Assessment</h2>
    <p>For technical roles, candidates may be required to complete an assessment:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Providing a coding test, case study, or project assignment.</li>
        <li>Evaluating the candidate's technical skills and problem-solving abilities.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>5. Final Interview</h2>
    <p>Selected candidates are invited for a final interview, which includes:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Meeting with the hiring manager and team members.</li>
        <li>Discussing cultural fit and long-term goals.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>6. Offer and Onboarding</h2>
    <p>Once a candidate is selected, the final steps are:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Extending a formal job offer.</li>
        <li>Completing onboarding procedures and paperwork.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="faq">Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)</h2>
    <h3>1. How long does the hiring process take?</h3>
    <p>The hiring process typically takes 2-4 weeks, depending on the role and the number of applicants.</p>

    <h3>2. Can I apply for multiple positions?</h3>
    <p>Yes, you can apply for multiple positions if you meet the qualifications for each role.</p>

    <h3>3. What should I prepare for the technical assessment?</h3>
    <p>For technical roles, you may need to demonstrate your coding skills, solve case studies, or complete a project assignment. Review the job description for specific requirements.</p>

    <h3>4. How will I know if I am selected for the next round?</h3>
    <p>You will be notified via email or phone if you are selected for the next round of the hiring process.</p>

